5619  // Create LocalIsolate/LocalHeap for the main thread and set state to Running.
5620  main_thread_local_isolate_.reset(new LocalIsolate(this, ThreadKind::kMain));
5621 
5622  {
5623  IgnoreLocalGCRequests ignore_gc_requests(heap());
5624  main_thread_local_heap()->Unpark();
5625  }
5626 
5627  // Requires a LocalHeap to be set up to register a GC epilogue callback.
5628  inner_pointer_to_code_cache_ = new InnerPointerToCodeCache(this);
5629

5631  wasm_code_look_up_cache_ = new wasm::WasmCodeLookupCache;
5632 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5633 
5634  // Lock clients_mutex_ in order to prevent shared GCs from other clients
5635  // during deserialization.
5636  std::optional<base::RecursiveMutexGuard> clients_guard;
5637

5639  clients_guard.emplace(
5640  &use_shared_space_isolate->global_safepoint()->clients_mutex_);
5641  use_shared_space_isolate->global_safepoint()->AppendClient(this);
5642  }
5643 
5644  shared_space_isolate_ = use_shared_space_isolate;
5645 
5646  isolate_data_.is_shared_space_isolate_flag_ = is_shared_space_isolate();
5647  isolate_data_.uses_shared_heap_flag_ = has_shared_space();
5648 
5649  if (use_shared_space_isolate && !is_shared_space_isolate() &&

5651  ->incremental_marking()

5653  heap_.SetIsMarkingFlag(true);
5654  }
5655

5657  DCHECK(!heap_.HasBeenSetUp());
5658  heap_.SetUp(main_thread_local_heap());

5660  if (!create_heap_objects) {
5661  // Must be done before deserializing RO space, since RO space may contain
5662  // builtin Code objects which point into the (potentially remapped)
5663  // embedded blob.
5664  MaybeRemapEmbeddedBuiltinsIntoCodeRange();
5665  }
5666  {
5667  // Must be done before deserializing RO space since the deserialization
5668  // process refers to these data structures.
5669  isolate_data_.external_reference_table()->InitIsolateIndependent(
5670  isolate_group()->external_ref_table());
5671 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5672  external_pointer_table().Initialize();

5674  heap()->read_only_external_pointer_space());
5675  external_pointer_table().AttachSpaceToReadOnlySegments(
5676  heap()->read_only_external_pointer_space());
5677  external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5678  heap()->young_external_pointer_space());
5679  external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5680  heap()->old_external_pointer_space());
5681  cpp_heap_pointer_table().Initialize();
5682  cpp_heap_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(heap()->cpp_heap_pointer_space());
5683 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5684

5686  trusted_pointer_table().Initialize();
5687  trusted_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(heap()->trusted_pointer_space());
5688 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5689  }

5691  heap_.SetUpSpaces(isolate_data_.new_allocation_info_,
5692  isolate_data_.old_allocation_info_);
5693 
5694  DCHECK_EQ(this, Isolate::Current());
5695  PerIsolateThreadData* const current_data = CurrentPerIsolateThreadData();
5696  DCHECK_EQ(current_data->isolate(), this);
5697  SetIsolateThreadLocals(this, current_data);
5698 
5699  if (OwnsStringTables()) {
5700  string_table_ = std::make_unique<StringTable>(this);
5701  string_forwarding_table_ = std::make_unique<StringForwardingTable>(this);
5702  } else {
5703  // Only refer to shared string table after attaching to the shared isolate.
5704  DCHECK(has_shared_space());
5705  DCHECK(!is_shared_space_isolate());
5706  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(string_table());
5707  DCHECK_NOT_NULL(string_forwarding_table());
5708  }
5709 
5710 #ifdef V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
5711  {
5712  VirtualMemoryCage* code_cage;
5713  if (heap_.code_range()) {
5714  code_cage = heap_.code_range();
5715  } else {
5716  CHECK(jitless_);
5717  // In jitless mode the code space pages will be allocated in the main
5718  // pointer compression cage.
5719  code_cage = isolate_group_->GetPtrComprCage();
5720  }
5721  code_cage_base_ = ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::PrepareCageBaseAddress(
5722  code_cage->base());
5723  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_IN_MULTIPLE_CAGES_BOOL) {
5724  // .. now that it's available, initialize the thread-local base.
5725  ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::InitBase(code_cage_base_);
5726  }
5727  CHECK_EQ(ExternalCodeCompressionScheme::base(), code_cage_base_);
5728 
5729  // Ensure that ExternalCodeCompressionScheme is applicable to all objects
5730  // stored in the code cage.
5731  using ComprScheme = ExternalCodeCompressionScheme;
5732  Address base = code_cage->base() + kHeapObjectTag;
5733  Address last = base + code_cage->size() - kTaggedSize;
5734  Address upper_bound = base + kPtrComprCageReservationSize - kTaggedSize;
5735  PtrComprCageBase code_cage_base{code_cage_base_};
5736  CHECK_EQ(base,
5737  ComprScheme::DecompressTagged(ComprScheme::CompressAny(base)));
5738  CHECK_EQ(last,
5739  ComprScheme::DecompressTagged(ComprScheme::CompressAny(last)));
5740  CHECK_EQ(upper_bound, ComprScheme::DecompressTagged(
5741  ComprScheme::CompressAny(upper_bound)));
5742  }
5743 #endif // V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE
5744 
5745  isolate_data_.external_reference_table()->Init(this);
5746 
5747 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5748  if (owns_shareable_data()) {
5749  isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_ = new ExternalPointerTable();
5750  shared_external_pointer_space_ = new ExternalPointerTable::Space();
5751  shared_external_pointer_table().Initialize();
5752  shared_external_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5753  shared_external_pointer_space());
5754  } else {
5755  DCHECK(has_shared_space());
5756  isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_ =
5757  shared_space_isolate()->isolate_data_.shared_external_pointer_table_;
5758  shared_external_pointer_space_ =
5759  shared_space_isolate()->shared_external_pointer_space_;
5760  }
5761 #endif // V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
5762 
5763 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5764  IsolateGroup::current()->code_pointer_table()->InitializeSpace(
5765  heap()->code_pointer_space());

5767  isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_ = new TrustedPointerTable();
5768  shared_trusted_pointer_space_ = new TrustedPointerTable::Space();
5769  shared_trusted_pointer_table().Initialize();
5770  shared_trusted_pointer_table().InitializeSpace(
5771  shared_trusted_pointer_space());
5772  } else {
5773  DCHECK(has_shared_space());
5774  isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_ =
5775  shared_space_isolate()->isolate_data_.shared_trusted_pointer_table_;
5776  shared_trusted_pointer_space_ =
5777  shared_space_isolate()->shared_trusted_pointer_space_;
5778  }
5779 
5780 #endif // V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX
5781 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5782  IsolateGroup::current()->js_dispatch_table()->InitializeSpace(
5783  heap()->js_dispatch_table_space());
5784 #endif // V8_ENABLE_LEAPTIERING
5785 
5786 #if V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5787  wasm::GetWasmEngine()->AddIsolate(this);
5788 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5789 
5790 #if defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5791  if (v8_flags.enable_etw_stack_walking ||
5792  v8_flags.enable_etw_by_custom_filter_only) {
5793  ETWJITInterface::AddIsolate(this);
5794  }
5795 #endif // defined(V8_ENABLE_ETW_STACK_WALKING)
5796 
5797  if (setup_delegate_ == nullptr) {
5798  setup_delegate_ = new SetupIsolateDelegate;
5799  }
5800 
5801  if (!v8_flags.inline_new) heap_.DisableInlineAllocation();
5802 
5803  if (!setup_delegate_->SetupHeap(this, create_heap_objects)) {
5804  V8::FatalProcessOutOfMemory(this, "heap object creation");
5805  }
5806 
5807  if (create_heap_objects) {
5808  // Terminate the startup and shared heap object caches so we can iterate.
5809  startup_object_cache_.push_back(ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
5810  shared_heap_object_cache_.push_back(ReadOnlyRoots(this).undefined_value());
5811  }

5820

5835  }

5857  }

5935  sample_interval, stack_depth, sampling_flags);
5936  }

5939  double ms = timer.Elapsed().InMillisecondsF();

5941  }

5984 
5985  initialized_ = true;
5986 
5987  return true;

5025  // Currently we call only ApiGetters from JS code.
5026  ReportExceptionPropertyCallback(Cast<JSReceiver>(holder), name,
5027  v8::ExceptionContext::kAttributeGet);
5028  return;

5034  return;

5036  case StackFrame::BUILTIN_EXIT:

5041  case StackFrame::WASM_SEGMENT_START:
5042  // No more info.
5043  return;
5044 #endif // V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
5045  default:
5046  // Other types are not expected, so just hard-crash.
